metadata.name: When We Touched
metadata.description:
With you, all that I am becomes a blubbering mess
A string of disjointed sentences amidst grave stuttering
With you, I see love, not for the joy it brings, but how far apart it tears us
With you, WE was a possibility because YOU and I did not like US
And US was YOU for both of US.
For when We touched, I became You and You, Me.
